<section class="ep-faq">
  <div class="ep-faq-inner">
    <div>
      <span class="ep-chapter-label">Common Questions</span>
      <h2 class="ep-faq-title">Retirement Income FAQ</h2>
      <p class="ep-faq-sub">Answers to the most common retirement income planning questions.</p>
      <a href="/contact/" class="ep-btn-ghost">Ask About Income Planning</a>
    </div>
    <div>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How much money do I need to retire comfortably? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>The answer depends on your desired lifestyle and expenses. A general rule is replacing 70-90% of your pre-retirement income. We analyze your specific expenses, Social Security benefits, and other income sources to determine your exact income gap and how much you need saved.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">What is the 4% withdrawal rule and is it still valid? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>The 4% rule suggests withdrawing 4% of your portfolio annually for a 30-year retirement. However, sequence of returns risk and today's low bond yields make this less reliable. We use dynamic withdrawal strategies that adjust based on market performance and portfolio balance.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do I avoid running out of money in retirement? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Avoid running out by diversifying income sources, using withdrawal sequencing strategies, maintaining adequate cash reserves, and building a guaranteed income floor with Social Security and potentially annuities. We stress-test your plan against various market scenarios.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">Should I annuitize part of my retirement savings? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Annuities can provide guaranteed income to cover essential expenses, reducing sequence of returns risk. However, they often have high fees and limited liquidity. We evaluate if annuities fit your situation and help select appropriate products if they do.</p></div>
      </button>
      <button class="ep-faq-item" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
        <span class="ep-faq-q">How do I coordinate Social Security with other retirement income? <span class="ep-faq-icon">+</span></span>
        <div class="ep-faq-a"><p>Social Security timing affects your overall income strategy. Delaying Social Security while using retirement accounts can increase lifetime benefits but requires careful tax planning. We model different claiming strategies to optimize your total retirement income.</p></div>
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

